name: Squats (Bodyweight)
description: A compound exercise that works the entire lower body. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, lower your hips as if sitting in a chair, keeping your chest up and back straight.

name: Deadlifts (Conventional)
description: A foundational strength exercise. Lift a barbell from the floor to a standing position, engaging your posterior chain. Focus on proper form to avoid injury.

name: Bench Press (Barbell)
description: Lie on a bench and press a barbell upwards from your chest. Great for building upper body strength and mass.

name: Overhead Press (Barbell)
description: Press a barbell overhead from shoulder height. Works the shoulders and helps build overall upper body stability.

name: Pull-ups
description: Hang from a bar with an overhand grip and pull your body up until your chin clears the bar. An excellent exercise for building back and bicep strength.

name: Lunges (Bodyweight)
description: Step forward with one leg and lower your hips until both knees are bent at approximately a 90-degree angle. Improves balance and leg strength.

name: Plank (Forearm)
description: Hold a position similar to the top of a push-up, supporting your body on your forearms and toes. Engages the entire core for stability.

name: Russian Twists
description: Sit on the floor with knees bent and feet lifted. Lean back slightly and twist your torso from side to side. Targets the obliques.

name: Dumbbell Bicep Curls
description: Stand or sit, holding dumbbells with palms facing forward. Curl the weights up towards your shoulders, squeezing your biceps.

name: Tricep Dips (Bench)
description: Use a bench to lower your body by bending your elbows, then push back up. Excellent for tricep development.

name: Push-ups (Standard)
description: Lie face down on the floor with hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Push up until your arms are straight, keeping your body in a straight line.

name: Rowing Machine
description: Simulates rowing a boat, providing a full-body cardiovascular and strength workout. Focus on a strong leg drive followed by a pull with your arms and back.

name: Burpees
description: A high-intensity exercise combining a squat, push-up, and jump. Excellent for building explosive power and cardiovascular endurance.

name: Leg Press
description: Sit on a leg press machine and push the platform away with your feet. Allows for heavy lifting to build leg strength with less stress on the back.

name: Lateral Raises (Dumbbell)
description: Hold dumbbells in each hand and raise them out to the sides until your arms are parallel to the floor. Isolates the side deltoid muscles.

name: Calf Raises (Standing)
description: Stand on the balls of your feet and raise your heels as high as possible. Targets the calf muscles.

name: Barbell Rows (Bent-Over)
description: Bend at the hips, keeping your back straight, and pull a barbell towards your lower chest. Excellent for building back thickness.

name: Leg Curls (Machine)
description: Lie face down on a machine and curl your legs towards your glutes. Isolates the hamstrings.

name: Leg Extensions (Machine)
description: Sit on a machine and extend your legs forward. Isolates the quadriceps.

name: Face Pulls (Cable)
description: Using a cable machine, pull a rope attachment towards your face, externally rotating your shoulders. Great for posture and shoulder health.

name: Glute Bridge
description: Lie on your back with knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Lift your hips off the ground, squeezing your glutes.

name: Crunches
description: Lie on your back, knees bent, and lift your upper body towards your knees, focusing on contracting the abs.

name: Bicycle Crunches
description: Lie on your back, bring knees towards chest, and alternate touching elbow to opposite knee, mimicking a cycling motion.

name: Tricep Pushdowns (Cable)
description: Using a cable machine, push a bar or rope attachment downwards, extending your arms. Isolates the triceps.

name: Hammer Curls (Dumbbell)
description: Hold dumbbells with palms facing each other and curl them up. Targets biceps and forearms differently than standard curls.

name: Box Jumps
description: Jump onto a sturdy box or platform, landing softly. Improves explosive power and cardiovascular fitness.

name: Mountain Climbers
description: Start in a plank position and rapidly bring your knees towards your chest one at a time. A dynamic core and cardio exercise.

name: Jump Squats
description: Perform a regular squat, then explode upwards into a jump. Adds a plyometric element to squats.

name: Good Mornings (Barbell)
description: With a barbell on your upper back, hinge at your hips, keeping legs almost straight, and lower your torso until it's almost parallel to the floor. Strengthens the posterior chain.

name: Pistol Squats
description: A single-leg squat, where one leg is extended forward. Requires significant balance and leg strength.

name: Yoga: Downward-Facing Dog
description: A foundational yoga pose that stretches the hamstrings, calves, and lengthens the spine. Forms an inverted 'V' shape with the body.

name: Skipping (Jump Rope)
description: A cardiovascular exercise using a jump rope. Improves coordination, agility, and endurance.

name: Kettlebell Swings
description: A ballistic exercise that builds explosive power in the posterior chain. Swing the kettlebell between your legs and then up to shoulder height, driving with the hips.

name: Walking Lunges (with Dumbbells)
description: Perform lunges while walking forward, holding dumbbells for added resistance. Builds leg strength and endurance.

name: Incline Dumbbell Press
description: Lie on an incline bench and press dumbbells upwards. Targets the upper chest more effectively.

name: Pull-aparts (Resistance Band)
description: Hold a resistance band with outstretched arms and pull it apart, squeezing your shoulder blades together. Improves posture and shoulder stability.
